headline: Is Texas Instruments (TXN) Pricing In Too Much Growth After Recent Share Price Strength
summary: Wondering if Texas Instruments at around US$196.59 is offering solid value or asking too much? This article is designed to help you make sense of the price tag before you make your next move. The stock has recently posted returns of 2.6% over 7 days, 11.1% over 30 days, 10.7% year to date, 8.5% over 1 year, 23.5% over 3 years, and 30.6% over 5 years. headline: Stifel Sees Signs of a Demand Recovery for Texas Instruments (TXN)
summary: Texas Instruments Incorporated (NASDAQ:TXN) is included among the 15 Best S&P 500 Dividend Stocks to Buy in 2026. On January 16, Stifel analyst Tore Svanberg raised Texas Instruments Incorporated (NASDAQ:TXN)’s price target to $200 from $170 and maintained a Hold rating on the stock.
